723627f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square - 14th Street - [Union Square Park.]
723627f-a.text:
Classification: Parks
UUnion Square, seen from the S.W. corner at University Place and 14th
Street, nearly identical in scene with the New York Ldison Company's
photograph No. 49767, taken in 1893. Most of the new buildings
shown here were erected between 1902 and 1910. The new Union
Square Savings Bank is on the N.E. conner of 15th Street, and the
11-story Reliance Building at 32 Union Square, adjoins the old

To the same period belong the Everett Building on the N.W. corner
of 17th Street and Fourth Avenue, and the Guardian Life Insurance
building (3riginally Germania Life Insurance) on the N.E. corner.
On the street floor of the old Union Scuare Hotel may be seen one

The principal change during these years, however, will be the

723607f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square (East) - 14th Street.
723607f-a.text:
Union Square East, from 8 Union Sduare (above 14th Street) to 34
Union Square at 16th Street, showing the expansion of S. Klein.
The Union Square Hotel is on the S.E. corner of 15th Street and the
Union Square Savings Bank on the N.W. corner.
February 24, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

708189f-a.title: Manhattan: 4th Avenue - 14th Street
708189f-a.text:
Fourth Ave., east side, south from East 14th to 11th Streets. On the
extreme left appears a portion of the Central Savings Bank Building at the
S.E. corner of East 14th Street.
June 11, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
